                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <ref target="#ms_i1.1 #ms_i1.2 #ms_i1.3"/>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <ref target="#ms_i1.4 #ms_i1.5"/>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works. Occasionally God is rubricated in alternating red and black letters (e.g., <locus target="#13r" facs="015"/>)
                  Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#92v" facs="095"/> (Ps. 145); <locus target="#93v" facs="096"/> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#101r #101v" facs="103 104"/> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1038Baptism">Baptism of Jesus</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d3">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#2v #9r #17v #24r #29r #37v #47r #59r #70r #80v #83r #88v #94r #104r #109v #110r #120v" facs="005 011 020 026 031 040 049 061 072 083 085 091 096 106 112 123"/> (ḥaräg);
                    <locus target="#54v" facs="057"/> (lines of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#113r #116v #120v" facs="115 119 123"/> (multiple full stops);
                    <locus target="#114v #115v" facs="117 118"/> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#117v" facs="120"/> (line of full stops between lines of alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(etco)" facs="001"/>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iv(erso) #121r #121v" facs="002 123 124"/>
                    scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#4r #7v #8r #11v" facs="006 009 014"/>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#65r #112v #116r #117v" facs="067 115 118 120"/>);
                      erasure markings are visible (e.g., <locus target="#4r #15r #25v" facs="006 017 028"/>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#60r #66v #90v" facs="062 069 091"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. Where the line of text is too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
